#!hexa strict
// qmirror/qfi-spin-motion/module/qfi_spin_motion.hexa
//
// @tool(slug="qmirror_qfi_spin_motion", desc="EXACT Quantum Fisher Information (QFI) F_phi := 4 Var(S_z) of adiabatic Tavis-Cummings spin-motion states. Pure-hexa engine: a self-contained spin (x) truncated-bosonic-mode complex state vector of dimension D = n_mode * 2^N (D <= 128 at N<=4, n_mode<=8) is initialized in |all-down>_spin (x) |squeezed-vacuum>_mode, evolved adiabatically under H_TC(t) = Delta(t) S_z + (lambda(t)/sqrt(N))(S+ a + S- a^dag) (Eq. (1) of arXiv:2411.10117) using 4th-order Runge-Kutta on the Schrodinger ODE i d|psi>/dt = H(t)|psi>, and the QFI for an unknown phase phi imprinted via R_z = exp(-i phi S_z) is the closed-form F_phi = 4*(<S_z^2> - <S_z>^2) on the final state. Three baselines computed at N in {1,2,3,4} and log-log fit recovers the scaling exponent: (i) product spin-coherent |+>^N (SQL alpha=1, exact F=N); (ii) GHZ (|0>^N + |1>^N)/sqrt(2) (Heisenberg alpha=2, exact F=N^2); (iii) Tavis-Cummings adiabatic state (super-Heisenberg alpha~5/2 per arXiv:2411.10117, finite-N range). Five falsifier invariants F1-F5: F1 alpha_SQL within (0.8, 1.2); F2 alpha_GHZ within (1.8, 2.2); F3 alpha_TC within (2.0, 3.0); F4 F_phi >= 0 always; F5 norm drift < 1e-9 across every state-vector operation. Genuine ceiling: the **truncated-bosonic-mode dimension** n_mode <= 8 (NOT the 2^N spin wall) -- states with high photon occupancy n > n_mode-1 are MISSED, which caps the achievable squeezing parameter r at ~ 1.5 (where sinh^2 r ~ 4.5 is well within n_mode=8). NOT a real-QPU trapped-ion / cavity-QED experiment; NOT the continuous-bosonic-mode regime; NOT the asymptotic large-N regime (the 5/2 exponent is fit over N in {1,2,3,4}); NOT a duplicate of any existing module -- this is the quantum-metrology / QFI axis (parameter estimation Cramer-Rao bound).")
// @usage(hexa run qfi-spin-motion/module/qfi_spin_motion.hexa --selftest)
// @sentinel(__QMIRROR_QFI_SPIN_MOTION__ <PASS|FAIL>)
// @resolver-bypass(reason="Selftest is a pure-hexa adiabatic-evolution kernel + closed-form QFI = 4 Var(S_z) reduction. No qiskit, no python bridge, no QRNG, no sampling; the verdict is the slope of a log-log linear fit on (N, F_phi) over N in {1,2,3,4}, with hard thresholds on alpha for the three baselines per arXiv:2411.10117 Eq. (1)/(5). Real-symmetric H_TC -> real-valued state throughout the adiabatic ramp -> norm drift = the only numerical drift; F5 monitors it.")
//
// =============================================================================
//  PAPER DEEP-DIVE  (WebFetch arxiv.org/abs/2411.10117 + html, 2026-05-17)
// =============================================================================
//
//  Recent (2024): "Quantum Fisher Information of adiabatic Tavis-Cummings
//  spin-motion states", arXiv:2411.10117. The paper claims super-Heisenberg
//  scaling
//
//      F_phi ~ N^{5/2}                                                       (headline)
//
//  for the QFI of an unknown phase phi imprinted by a collective-S_z
//  rotation R_z = exp(-i phi S_z) on a spin-motion state prepared by
//  ADIABATIC EVOLUTION under the time-dependent Tavis-Cummings Hamiltonian
//
//      H_TC(t)  =  Delta(t) S_z  +  (lambda(t) / sqrt(N)) ( S+ a  +  S- a^dag )    (Eq. (1))
//
//  with N = number of spin-1/2 atoms, S = N/2, S_z / S+ / S- collective
//  angular-momentum operators, a / a^dag bosonic ladder. The ramp:
//
//      Delta(t)  = Delta_0 sin( gamma t / 2 )                                (paper p.2)
//      lambda(t) = lambda_0 cos^2( gamma t / 2 )                             (paper p.2)
//
//  drives Delta from large NEGATIVE to large POSITIVE while
//  |Delta(t)| >> lambda(t) is maintained (the dispersive condition).
//
//  INITIAL STATE  (paper Eq. just above (1)):
//
//      |psi(t_i)>  =  |S, -S>  (x)  |zeta>                                   (initial)
//
//  i.e. all spins in their lowest m=-S state (collective ground state along
//  -z) tensored with a SQUEEZED VACUUM of the bosonic mode, |zeta> =
//  S(r) |0>_mode, S(r) the standard one-mode squeeze operator with real
//  squeezing parameter r. In the Fock basis (paper / Gerry-Knight 2004):
//
//      |zeta>  =  (1 / sqrt(cosh r))  *  Sum_{k=0..inf}  sqrt((2k)!) / (2^k k!)
//                                         * (- tanh r)^k  |2k>               (Fock expansion)
//
//  (only EVEN Fock components; truncation at k_max = (n_mode-1)/2).
//
//  ASYMPTOTIC HEADLINE (paper Eq. (5), z := tanh^2 r -> 1):
//
//      F_phi^max  =  ( 256 sqrt(1 - z) / (15 sqrt(pi)) ) * (N/2)^{5/2}        (Eq. (5))
//
//  i.e. the exponent is EXACTLY 5/2 in the strong-squeezing limit z -> 1.
//  Figure 3(b) shows Region I exhibiting the N^{5/2} scaling for r ~= 2.5
//  out to N ~ 20-30, beyond which the scaling crosses over to a saturated
//  Region II.
//
//  PARAMETER ESTIMATED  (paper, just above Eq. (3)):
//      "An unknown phase phi, the parameter we wish to estimate, is imprinted
//       by a collective rotation about the z-axis, described by
//       R_z = exp(-i phi S_z)."
//
//  PURE-STATE QFI CLOSED FORM (Generator-rotation case):
//
//      F_phi(|psi>) = 4 * ( <psi| S_z^2 |psi>  -  <psi| S_z |psi>^2 )       (Caves-Helstrom 1994)
//                   = 4 * Var(S_z) on |psi> .
//
//  Hence the QFI is an EXPECTATION VALUE on the prepared state -- no finite
//  differences needed.
//
// =============================================================================
//  HONEST SCOPE  (@D g1 / @D g5 / @D g6 / @D g7 / @F f1)
// =============================================================================
//
//  This module is an EXACT 2^N * n_mode-amplitude complex-state-vector
//  simulation of the Tavis-Cummings adiabatic protocol of arXiv:2411.10117
//  on a truncated bosonic mode. It is faithful to the paper's *adiabatic
//  state-preparation + collective-rotation generator* mathematical object on
//  the exactly-reachable register. It is:
//
//   - NOT a real-QPU trapped-ion / cavity-QED experiment. No spontaneous
//     emission, no motional heating, no laser-phase noise, no SPAM, no
//     finite-shot tomography or finite-shot Cramer-Rao saturation.
//
//   - NOT the continuous-bosonic-mode regime. The bosonic Hilbert space is
//     TRUNCATED at n_mode <= 8 Fock states. The genuine ceiling is the
//     TRUNCATION dimension (NOT the 2^N spin wall): squeezed vacua with
//     sinh^2(r) > n_mode - 1 ~= 7 photons are missed. We therefore use
//     modest squeezing r in [0.8, 1.2] (sinh^2 r in [0.86, 2.27] photons,
//     comfortably within n_mode=8 and adequate for the dispersive transfer
//     to spin squeezing at small N).
//
//   - NOT the asymptotic large-N regime. The N^{5/2} scaling is the
//     strong-squeezing (z -> 1) ASYMPTOTIC of paper Eq. (5); at finite N
//     in {1,2,3,4} with modest r, the recovered slope is a FINITE-N
//     truncation of the asymptotic exponent. Our F3 threshold (2.0 < alpha
//     < 3.0) accepts the entire super-Heisenberg band and guards the
//     algebraic ceiling alpha <= 3 (one-body operator QFI on N spins
//     cannot exceed N^3 by a Schur-bound argument). At our register size
//     and squeezing, we expect alpha in [2.2, 2.7].
//
//   - NOT a duplicate of any existing qmirror module. The QFI / quantum-
//     metrology axis (parameter estimation, Cramer-Rao bound, Caves-Helstrom
//     1994) is orthogonal to CDR / shadows / DFE / magic-monotone /
//     stabilizer-extent / Loschmidt-rate / etc. ones currently in the
//     repository.
//
//  Reachable results -- the exact closed-form SQL slope alpha=1 (product
//  spin-coherent state) and the exact closed-form Heisenberg slope alpha=2
//  (GHZ) -- are claimed exactly, never down-played; they are the two
//  CLOSED-FORM ANCHORS for the falsifier invariants F1 and F2.
//
// =============================================================================
//  FILE OWNERSHIP / DROP-IN COMPAT  (@D g7)
// =============================================================================
//
//  NEW sibling module. Does NOT touch engine_aer / qrng / chsh / iit_mip
//  external signatures (the spin x truncated-mode state vector is a custom
//  flat [float] in-module representation; we do NOT abuse engine_aer's
//  power-of-2-only kernel for a non-power-of-2 D = n_mode * 2^N). Pure-hexa
//  runtime; NO .py / qiskit / qiskit-aer / qiskit-nature / pyscf / pyphi
//  dependency (@D g5). Falsifier-first marker emission (@D g6) -- the
//  FAILED.marker write path runs BEFORE the pass marker.
//
// ── hexa quirks honored ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
//   - >= / <= banned -- strict < / > / == only. (Use `if a > b - 1` for a >= b.)
//   - struct names cannot start with _.
//   - no `break` -- flag-driven while loops.
//   - power-of-two via while loop (no builtin).
//   - Math builtins exp / log / sin / cos / sqrt / tanh / pow / atan2 / log2
//     are available; cosh / sinh are NOT exposed in the qmirror hexa-lang
//     interpreter dispatch (codegen_c2 supports them but the interpreter
//     dispatch lacks the entries). We inline:
//         cosh(r) := (exp(r) + exp(-r)) / 2
//         sinh(r) := (exp(r) - exp(-r)) / 2
//     using the exposed `exp` builtin (`tanh` IS exposed and we use it).

// =============================================================================
//  §1  SCALAR HELPERS
// =============================================================================

fn qfi_absf(x: float) -> float {
    if x < 0.0 { return 0.0 - x }
    return x
}

// hyperbolic helpers (cosh / sinh are not exposed by the interpreter)
fn qfi_cosh(x: float) -> float {
    let ep = exp(x)
    let em = exp(0.0 - x)
    return 0.5 * (ep + em)
}
fn qfi_sinh(x: float) -> float {
    let ep = exp(x)
    let em = exp(0.0 - x)
    return 0.5 * (ep - em)
}
fn qfi_tanh(x: float) -> float {
    let ep = exp(x)
    let em = exp(0.0 - x)
    return (ep - em) / (ep + em)
}

fn qfi_max2(a: float, b: float) -> float {
    if a < b { return b }
    return a
}

fn qfi_min2(a: float, b: float) -> float {
    if a < b { return a }
    return b
}

// 2^n  (no power-of-two builtin)
fn qfi_pow2(n: int) -> int {
    let mut d = 1
    let mut k = 0
    while k < n { d = d * 2; k = k + 1 }
    return d
}

// integer pow: base^exp  (exp >= 0)
fn qfi_ipow(base: int, exp: int) -> int {
    let mut p = 1
    let mut k = 0
    while k < exp { p = p * base; k = k + 1 }
    return p
}

// float pow via the hexa pow builtin
fn qfi_powf(base: float, exp: float) -> float {
    return pow(base, exp)
}

// integer factorial n! as float (for n up to ~16; we use it for at most n=8)
fn qfi_factorial_f(n: int) -> float {
    let mut p = 1.0
    let mut k = 1
    while k < n + 1 { p = p * to_float(k); k = k + 1 }
    return p
}

// double factorial (2k-1)!! = 1*3*5*...*(2k-1); (2*0-1)!! := 1.
fn qfi_double_factorial_odd_f(k: int) -> float {
    let mut p = 1.0
    let mut j = 1
    while j < 2 * k {
        p = p * to_float(j)
        j = j + 2
    }
    return p
}

// =============================================================================
//  §2  SPIN-MOTION FLAT-VECTOR REPRESENTATION
// =============================================================================
//
//  The Hilbert space is  H_mode (x) H_spin  with
//      dim_mode = n_mode    (truncated Fock basis |0>, |1>, ..., |n_mode-1>)
//      dim_spin = 2^N       (computational basis |s_{N-1} ... s_1 s_0>)
//      D        = n_mode * 2^N
//
//  A flat index  i = m * dim_spin + s   encodes  (m, s)  with the photon
//  number m as the SLOW axis and the spin string s as the FAST axis. Bit
//  q (q = 0..N-1) of s is the z-component of spin q: 0 = down (m_q = -1/2),
//  1 = up (m_q = +1/2). The collective operator
//
//      S_z = (1/2) Sum_q (n_q - (1-n_q)) = Sum_q s_q - N/2
//
//  i.e. <s|S_z|s> = popcount(s) - N/2.
//
//  Collective ladder operators:
//      S+ |s> = Sum_{q: s_q = 0} |s XOR (1<<q)>      (raises spin q)
//      S- |s> = Sum_{q: s_q = 1} |s XOR (1<<q)>      (lowers spin q)
//
//  (Note: NO sqrt prefactors for spin-1/2; these are the bare sums of
//  single-spin sigma+ / sigma- operators, consistent with paper Eq. (1).)
//
//  Bosonic ladder:
//      a |m>   = sqrt(m) |m-1>          (m > 0; a |0> = 0)
//      a^dag |m> = sqrt(m+1) |m+1>      (m < n_mode-1; otherwise truncated to 0)
//
//  H_TC matrix elements are then sparse: for fixed (Delta, lambda, N, n_mode)
//  the action H |i> -> sum_j H_{j,i} |j>  visits at most
//      1 (diagonal)  +  2 N  (each spin can be raised or lowered, possibly
//                              changing photon number by +/-1)
//  entries per i, well below the dense D^2 cost.

fn qfi_popcount(s: int, N: int) -> int {
    let mut c = 0
    let mut q = 0
    while q < N {
        if ((s >> q) & 1) == 1 { c = c + 1 }
        q = q + 1
    }
    return c
}

// S_z eigenvalue on computational-basis string s.
fn qfi_sz_value(s: int, N: int) -> float {
    return to_float(qfi_popcount(s, N)) - to_float(N) / 2.0
}

// =============================================================================
//  §3  SPARSE H_TC ACTION  (out += H_TC(Delta, lambda, N, n_mode) * v)
// =============================================================================
//
//  Real-valued H_TC: in the chosen basis, every matrix element is real
//  (Delta S_z is diagonal real; the (S+ a + S- a^dag) coupling is real-
//  symmetric since both off-diagonal terms are real and Hermitian). So
//  the action splits into a real-on-real + real-on-imag pair (the imag
//  channel obeys the same kernel as the real channel).
//
//  Side effect: ACCUMULATES into (out_re, out_im) (caller zero-fills first).

fn qfi_apply_H_tc(v_re: [float], v_im: [float],
                  out_re: [float], out_im: [float],
                  Delta: float, lambda_t: float,
                  N: int, n_mode: int) -> int {
    let dim_spin = qfi_pow2(N)
    let coupling = lambda_t / sqrt(to_float(N))
    // 1. Diagonal:  Delta * S_z
    let mut m = 0
    while m < n_mode {
        let mut s = 0
        while s < dim_spin {
            let i = m * dim_spin + s
            let sz = qfi_sz_value(s, N)
            let d = Delta * sz
            out_re[i] = out_re[i] + d * v_re[i]
            out_im[i] = out_im[i] + d * v_im[i]
            s = s + 1
        }
        m = m + 1
    }
    // 2. S+ a term:  applied to (m, s) -- requires m > 0, and any q with s_q=0.
    //    Produces (m-1, s XOR (1<<q))  with prefactor  coupling * sqrt(m).
    //    The matrix element <m-1, s'|H|m,s> contributes to OUT at index (m-1, s').
    let mut m1 = 1
    while m1 < n_mode {
        let pre_a = coupling * sqrt(to_float(m1))
        let mut s = 0
        while s < dim_spin {
            let i_in = m1 * dim_spin + s
            let mut q = 0
            while q < N {
                if ((s >> q) & 1) == 0 {
                    // raise spin q
                    let s_out = s ^ (1 << q)
                    let i_out = (m1 - 1) * dim_spin + s_out
                    out_re[i_out] = out_re[i_out] + pre_a * v_re[i_in]
                    out_im[i_out] = out_im[i_out] + pre_a * v_im[i_in]
                }
                q = q + 1
            }
            s = s + 1
        }
        m1 = m1 + 1
    }
    // 3. S- a^dag term: applied to (m, s) -- requires m < n_mode-1 AND any q with s_q=1.
    //    Produces (m+1, s XOR (1<<q))  with prefactor  coupling * sqrt(m+1).
    let mut m2 = 0
    while m2 < n_mode - 1 {
        let pre_ad = coupling * sqrt(to_float(m2 + 1))
        let mut s = 0
        while s < dim_spin {
            let i_in = m2 * dim_spin + s
            let mut q = 0
            while q < N {
                if ((s >> q) & 1) == 1 {
                    let s_out = s ^ (1 << q)
                    let i_out = (m2 + 1) * dim_spin + s_out
                    out_re[i_out] = out_re[i_out] + pre_ad * v_re[i_in]
                    out_im[i_out] = out_im[i_out] + pre_ad * v_im[i_in]
                }
                q = q + 1
            }
            s = s + 1
        }
        m2 = m2 + 1
    }
    return 0
}

// =============================================================================
//  §4  SQUEEZED VACUUM IN FOCK BASIS
// =============================================================================
//
//  S(r) |0>_mode  =  (1/sqrt(cosh r)) Sum_{k=0}^inf  sqrt((2k)!) / (2^k k!)
//                                                   * (- tanh r)^k  |2k>
//
//  Using (2k)! = (2k)!! * (2k-1)!!  and  (2k)!! = 2^k k!  gives
//  sqrt((2k)!) / (2^k k!) = sqrt((2k-1)!! / (2k)!!) = sqrt( prod_{j=1..k} (2j-1)/(2j) ),
//  but we use the direct factorial form here for clarity (k <= 4 at n_mode<=8).
//
//  Returns a fresh ([float], [float]) pair of length D = n_mode * 2^N with
//  the squeezed-mode amplitudes in the m index and zero spin string s=0
//  (all spins down).

struct AmpPair {
    re: [float],
    im: [float],
    D:  int
}

fn qfi_state_zero(N: int, n_mode: int) -> AmpPair {
    let dim_spin = qfi_pow2(N)
    let D = n_mode * dim_spin
    let mut re = []
    let mut im = []
    let mut i = 0
    while i < D {
        re = re.push(0.0)
        im = im.push(0.0)
        i = i + 1
    }
    return AmpPair { re: re, im: im, D: D }
}

fn qfi_state_squeezed_vacuum_allspindown(r: float, N: int, n_mode: int) -> AmpPair {
    let dim_spin = qfi_pow2(N)
    let D = n_mode * dim_spin
    let mut re = []
    let mut im = []
    let mut i = 0
    while i < D {
        re = re.push(0.0)
        im = im.push(0.0)
        i = i + 1
    }
    let cosh_r = qfi_cosh(r)
    let tanh_r = qfi_tanh(r)
    let pref0 = 1.0 / sqrt(cosh_r)
    // k_max = floor((n_mode - 1) / 2)
    let mut k = 0
    let mut flag = 1
    while flag == 1 {
        let m = 2 * k
        if m > n_mode - 1 {
            flag = 0
        } else {
            let fact_2k = qfi_factorial_f(m)
            let fact_k  = qfi_factorial_f(k)
            let pow_2k  = qfi_powf(2.0, to_float(k))
            let coef = sqrt(fact_2k) / (pow_2k * fact_k)
            let sign = if (k % 2) == 0 { 1.0 } else { 0.0 - 1.0 }
            let pow_tanh = qfi_powf(tanh_r, to_float(k))
            let amp = pref0 * coef * sign * pow_tanh
            // place at (photon=m, spin=0)
            let idx = m * dim_spin + 0
            re[idx] = amp
            k = k + 1
        }
    }
    // RENORMALIZE the truncated squeezed-vacuum so |psi|^2 = 1 exactly.
    // The closed-form Fock expansion is infinite; truncating at m=n_mode-1
    // discards a tail of weight ~ tanh^{2*n_mode} / cosh(r) (small but not
    // zero), which would otherwise show up as a constant initial-norm
    // deficit and confound the RK4 drift witness F5. The renormalisation is
    // the standard / physically meaningful operation: a TRUNCATED squeezed
    // state inside a finite-dim Fock space is the projector of the exact
    // continuous-mode state onto |0>..|n_mode-1>, NORMALISED in that
    // subspace. The truncation is the honest-scope ceiling (@D g1) -- we
    // report the magnitude of the discarded tail as INFO in the selftest.
    let mut nsq = 0.0
    let mut j = 0
    while j < D {
        nsq = nsq + re[j] * re[j]
        j = j + 1
    }
    let nf = sqrt(nsq)
    if nf > 1.0e-30 {
        let mut p = 0
        while p < D {
            re[p] = re[p] / nf
            p = p + 1
        }
    }
    return AmpPair { re: re, im: im, D: D }
}

// Returns the (unrenormalised) squeezed-vacuum tail weight
// 1 - Sum_{k: 2k<n_mode} |c_{2k}|^2
// as the analytic INFO witness for the truncation @D g1.
fn qfi_squeezed_truncation_tail(r: float, n_mode: int) -> float {
    let cosh_r = qfi_cosh(r)
    let tanh_r = qfi_tanh(r)
    let pref0 = 1.0 / sqrt(cosh_r)
    let mut s = 0.0
    let mut k = 0
    let mut flag = 1
    while flag == 1 {
        let m = 2 * k
        if m > n_mode - 1 {
            flag = 0
        } else {
            let fact_2k = qfi_factorial_f(m)
            let fact_k  = qfi_factorial_f(k)
            let pow_2k  = qfi_powf(2.0, to_float(k))
            let coef = sqrt(fact_2k) / (pow_2k * fact_k)
            let pow_tanh = qfi_powf(tanh_r, to_float(k))
            let amp = pref0 * coef * pow_tanh
            s = s + amp * amp
            k = k + 1
        }
    }
    return 1.0 - s
}

// Norm <psi|psi> as a sanity number.
fn qfi_norm_sq(ap: AmpPair) -> float {
    let mut s = 0.0
    let mut i = 0
    while i < ap.D {
        s = s + ap.re[i] * ap.re[i] + ap.im[i] * ap.im[i]
        i = i + 1
    }
    return s
}

// =============================================================================
//  §5  4TH-ORDER RUNGE-KUTTA ON THE SCHRODINGER ODE
// =============================================================================
//
//      d|psi>/dt = -i H(t) |psi>
//
//  Real H(t) -> the formal -i splits into  d psi_re / dt = + H(t) psi_im
//                                          d psi_im / dt = - H(t) psi_re
//
//  Standard RK4 over a small dt; H is recomputed at t, t+dt/2 (twice), t+dt.
//  Norm is NOT exactly preserved -- monitored at every selftest step.
//
//  Helper: form k_re, k_im = -i H(t) |psi>  as flat [float] pairs.

// In-place form: writes  k_re = +(H psi)_im,  k_im = -(H psi)_re
// into PRE-ALLOCATED k_re / k_im buffers (caller zero-fills NEITHER --
// we zero them here, then apply_H_tc accumulates, then we swap-and-flip).
// Uses a scratch (tmp_re, tmp_im) buffer also passed by handle.
fn qfi_minus_i_H_psi_inplace(re_in: [float], im_in: [float],
                              k_re: [float], k_im: [float],
                              tmp_re: [float], tmp_im: [float],
                              Delta: float, lambda_t: float,
                              N: int, n_mode: int) -> int {
    let D = len(re_in)
    let mut i = 0
    while i < D {
        tmp_re[i] = 0.0
        tmp_im[i] = 0.0
        i = i + 1
    }
    let _ = qfi_apply_H_tc(re_in, im_in, tmp_re, tmp_im, Delta, lambda_t, N, n_mode)
    // d psi_re / dt = + (H psi)_im   ;  d psi_im / dt = - (H psi)_re
    let mut j = 0
    while j < D {
        k_re[j] = tmp_im[j]
        k_im[j] = 0.0 - tmp_re[j]
        j = j + 1
    }
    return 0
}

// Ramp closures
fn qfi_Delta_at(Delta0: float, gamma: float, t: float) -> float {
    return Delta0 * sin(gamma * t / 2.0)
}

fn qfi_lambda_at(lambda0: float, gamma: float, t: float) -> float {
    let c = cos(gamma * t / 2.0)
    return lambda0 * c * c
}

// In-place RK4 step: mutates (re, im) in place to hold the state at t + dt.
// Caller supplies eight scratch buffers (k1_re, k1_im, k2_re, k2_im, k3_re,
// k3_im, k4_re, k4_im) plus two more (y_re, y_im) for the intermediate
// y2 / y3 / y4 states plus two (tmp_re, tmp_im) used inside
// qfi_minus_i_H_psi_inplace. All twelve buffers are length D. No
// allocations in the hot loop -- this lets us run n_step >> 1000 without
// inflating RSS.
fn qfi_rk4_step_inplace(re: [float], im: [float],
                        k1_re: [float], k1_im: [float],
                        k2_re: [float], k2_im: [float],
                        k3_re: [float], k3_im: [float],
                        k4_re: [float], k4_im: [float],
                        y_re:  [float], y_im:  [float],
                        tmp_re: [float], tmp_im: [float],
                        t: float, dt: float,
                        Delta0: float, lambda0: float, gamma: float,
                        N: int, n_mode: int) -> int {
    let D = len(re)
    let Dh = qfi_Delta_at(Delta0, gamma, t)
    let Lh = qfi_lambda_at(lambda0, gamma, t)
    let _r1 = qfi_minus_i_H_psi_inplace(re, im, k1_re, k1_im, tmp_re, tmp_im, Dh, Lh, N, n_mode)
    // y2 = y + (dt/2) k1
    let mut i = 0
    while i < D {
        y_re[i] = re[i] + 0.5 * dt * k1_re[i]
        y_im[i] = im[i] + 0.5 * dt * k1_im[i]
        i = i + 1
    }
    let Dm = qfi_Delta_at(Delta0, gamma, t + 0.5 * dt)
    let Lm = qfi_lambda_at(lambda0, gamma, t + 0.5 * dt)
    let _r2 = qfi_minus_i_H_psi_inplace(y_re, y_im, k2_re, k2_im, tmp_re, tmp_im, Dm, Lm, N, n_mode)
    // y3 = y + (dt/2) k2
    let mut j = 0
    while j < D {
        y_re[j] = re[j] + 0.5 * dt * k2_re[j]
        y_im[j] = im[j] + 0.5 * dt * k2_im[j]
        j = j + 1
    }
    let _r3 = qfi_minus_i_H_psi_inplace(y_re, y_im, k3_re, k3_im, tmp_re, tmp_im, Dm, Lm, N, n_mode)
    // y4 = y + dt k3
    let mut p = 0
    while p < D {
        y_re[p] = re[p] + dt * k3_re[p]
        y_im[p] = im[p] + dt * k3_im[p]
        p = p + 1
    }
    let Df = qfi_Delta_at(Delta0, gamma, t + dt)
    let Lf = qfi_lambda_at(lambda0, gamma, t + dt)
    let _r4 = qfi_minus_i_H_psi_inplace(y_re, y_im, k4_re, k4_im, tmp_re, tmp_im, Df, Lf, N, n_mode)
    // y_new = y + (dt/6)(k1 + 2 k2 + 2 k3 + k4)
    let mut q = 0
    while q < D {
        let dre = (k1_re[q] + 2.0 * k2_re[q] + 2.0 * k3_re[q] + k4_re[q]) / 6.0
        let dim_ = (k1_im[q] + 2.0 * k2_im[q] + 2.0 * k3_im[q] + k4_im[q]) / 6.0
        re[q] = re[q] + dt * dre
        im[q] = im[q] + dt * dim_
        q = q + 1
    }
    return 0
}

// Run the full adiabatic ramp over t in [0, t_final] in n_steps RK4 steps.
// Returns the final state. Includes a final norm-renormalisation to absorb
// the O(dt^4) RK4 unitarity drift (we report the pre-renormalisation drift
// as F5 evidence -- the renorm is purely cosmetic for downstream QFI).
struct RampResult {
    state: AmpPair,
    norm_drift_max: float
}

fn qfi_adiabatic_ramp(init: AmpPair, t_start: float, t_range: float, n_steps: int,
                      Delta0: float, lambda0: float, gamma: float,
                      N: int, n_mode: int) -> RampResult {
    let D = init.D
    // Allocate state + 12 scratch buffers ONCE (each length D).
    let mut re = []
    let mut im = []
    let mut k1_re = []
    let mut k1_im = []
    let mut k2_re = []
    let mut k2_im = []
    let mut k3_re = []
    let mut k3_im = []
    let mut k4_re = []
    let mut k4_im = []
    let mut y_re  = []
    let mut y_im  = []
    let mut tmp_re = []
    let mut tmp_im = []
    let mut i = 0
    while i < D {
        re = re.push(init.re[i])
        im = im.push(init.im[i])
        k1_re = k1_re.push(0.0)
        k1_im = k1_im.push(0.0)
        k2_re = k2_re.push(0.0)
        k2_im = k2_im.push(0.0)
        k3_re = k3_re.push(0.0)
        k3_im = k3_im.push(0.0)
        k4_re = k4_re.push(0.0)
        k4_im = k4_im.push(0.0)
        y_re  = y_re.push(0.0)
        y_im  = y_im.push(0.0)
        tmp_re = tmp_re.push(0.0)
        tmp_im = tmp_im.push(0.0)
        i = i + 1
    }
    let dt = t_range / to_float(n_steps)
    let mut t = t_start
    let mut max_drift = 0.0
    let mut step = 0
    while step < n_steps {
        let _ = qfi_rk4_step_inplace(re, im,
                                      k1_re, k1_im, k2_re, k2_im,
                                      k3_re, k3_im, k4_re, k4_im,
                                      y_re, y_im, tmp_re, tmp_im,
                                      t, dt, Delta0, lambda0, gamma, N, n_mode)
        // measure norm drift
        let mut ns = 0.0
        let mut k = 0
        while k < D {
            ns = ns + re[k] * re[k] + im[k] * im[k]
            k = k + 1
        }
        let drift = qfi_absf(ns - 1.0)
        if drift > max_drift { max_drift = drift }
        t = t + dt
        step = step + 1
    }
    // Final cosmetic renorm so downstream <S_z>, <S_z^2> are taken on a
    // bona fide normalised state (F5 still reports the pre-renorm drift).
    let mut ns2 = 0.0
    let mut k2 = 0
    while k2 < D {
        ns2 = ns2 + re[k2] * re[k2] + im[k2] * im[k2]
        k2 = k2 + 1
    }
    let nf = sqrt(ns2)
    if nf > 1.0e-30 {
        let mut k3 = 0
        while k3 < D {
            re[k3] = re[k3] / nf
            im[k3] = im[k3] / nf
            k3 = k3 + 1
        }
    }
    return RampResult {
        state: AmpPair { re: re, im: im, D: D },
        norm_drift_max: max_drift
    }
}

// =============================================================================
//  §5b  CLOSED-FORM ADIABATIC FINAL-STATE QFI  (paper Eq. (4) verbatim)
// =============================================================================
//
//  The TC Hamiltonian commutes with the excitation number N_e = a^dag a + S_z + S
//  (paper line 153). The initial state |psi(t_i)> = |S,-S> (x) |zeta> =
//  Sum_n a_{2n} |S,-S>|2n>, is an exact superposition of 2n-excitation
//  eigenstates of H_TC(t_i) (since |Delta(t_i)| >> lambda(t_i) makes
//  Delta S_z dominate). Adiabatic following preserves the per-block state
//  identity, and the paper proves (line 164) that the corresponding final
//  state at large positive Delta is
//
//      |psi_2n(t_f)>  =  |S, -S + 2n> |0>            for 2n <= 2S
//                     =  |S,  S> |2n - 2S>           for 2n >  2S
//
//  so the final state is
//
//      |psi(t_f)>  =  Sum_{n: 2n<=2S} c_{2n} |S, -S+2n>|0>
//                    +  Sum_{n: 2n>2S}  c_{2n} |S,  S>|2n - 2S>
//
//  with the adiabatic-phase-decorated amplitudes c_{2n} = a_{2n} exp(-i eps_n)
//  (the phase has no effect on |c|^2 and therefore none on Var(S_z), so it
//  is irrelevant to the QFI).
//
//  Using paper Eq. (4) verbatim:
//
//      Var(S_z)  =  Sum_{n: 2n<=2S} |c_{2n}|^2 (-S + 2n)^2
//                 + S^2 * Sum_{n: 2n>2S}  |c_{2n}|^2
//                 - [ Sum_{n: 2n<=2S} |c_{2n}|^2 (-S + 2n)
//                    + S * Sum_{n: 2n>2S} |c_{2n}|^2 ]^2
//
//  F_phi = 4 * Var(S_z). This routine evaluates the closed form on the
//  TRUNCATED squeezed-vacuum amplitudes |c_{2n}|^2 = |a_{2n}|^2 / N_trunc
//  (N_trunc = norm of the truncated sum), so it inherits the same
//  finite-n_mode controlled approximation as the RK4 path. The match
//  RK4 == closed-form is verified as F6 (a soft-info invariant, not a gate)
//  for the small (N, n_mode) cases where RK4 is tractable.

struct ClosedFormResult {
    var_sz:    float,
    e_sz:      float,
    e_sz2:     float,
    qfi:       float,
    norm:      float,           // truncated-renormalised sum of |c_{2n}|^2 (= 1.0)
    tail:      float            // 1 - Sum_{2n <= n_mode-1} |a_{2n}|^2 (pre-renorm)
}

fn qfi_closed_form_adiabatic(r: float, N: int, n_mode: int) -> ClosedFormResult {
    // 1. Compute |a_{2k}|^2 for k = 0..floor((n_mode-1)/2)  (pre-renorm)
    let cosh_r = qfi_cosh(r)
    let tanh_r = qfi_tanh(r)
    let mut probs = []           // |a_{2k}|^2  for k = 0..k_max
    let mut k = 0
    let mut flag = 1
    while flag == 1 {
        let m = 2 * k
        if m > n_mode - 1 {
            flag = 0
        } else {
            let fact_2k = qfi_factorial_f(m)
            let fact_k  = qfi_factorial_f(k)
            let pow_2k  = qfi_powf(2.0, to_float(k))
            let coef = sqrt(fact_2k) / (pow_2k * fact_k)
            let pow_tanh = qfi_powf(tanh_r, to_float(k))
            let amp = (1.0 / sqrt(cosh_r)) * coef * pow_tanh
            probs = probs.push(amp * amp)
            k = k + 1
        }
    }
    // 2. Renormalize  (the truncation discards a high-k tail; the closed-form
    //    physical state is the projection onto |0>..|n_mode-1>, normalised)
    let mut pre_sum = 0.0
    let mut i0 = 0
    while i0 < len(probs) {
        pre_sum = pre_sum + probs[i0]
        i0 = i0 + 1
    }
    let tail = 1.0 - pre_sum
    let mut q = 0
    while q < len(probs) {
        probs[q] = probs[q] / pre_sum
        q = q + 1
    }
    // 3. Compute Var(S_z) via Eq. (4)
    //    S = N/2 ; for 2k <= 2S = N  spin m_z = -S + 2k ; for 2k > 2S spin m_z = +S.
    let S = to_float(N) / 2.0
    let mut e1 = 0.0
    let mut e2 = 0.0
    let mut j = 0
    while j < len(probs) {
        let two_k = 2 * j
        let mz = if two_k < N + 1 {        // 2k <= N (i.e. <= 2S)
            0.0 - S + to_float(two_k)
        } else {
            S
        }
        e1 = e1 + probs[j] * mz
        e2 = e2 + probs[j] * mz * mz
        j = j + 1
    }
    let var_sz = e2 - e1 * e1
    return ClosedFormResult {
        var_sz: var_sz,
        e_sz:   e1,
        e_sz2:  e2,
        qfi:    4.0 * var_sz,
        norm:   1.0,
        tail:   tail
    }
}

// =============================================================================
//  §6  EXPECTATIONS  <S_z> and <S_z^2>   (closed form on the flat amps)
// =============================================================================
//
//  S_z is diagonal in the chosen basis, so
//
//      <S_z>    = Sum_i |amp_i|^2 * S_z_value(s_i, N)
//      <S_z^2>  = Sum_i |amp_i|^2 * S_z_value(s_i, N)^2
//
//  where s_i = i mod dim_spin (the FAST axis).

struct SzMoments {
    e_sz:   float,
    e_sz2:  float,
    var_sz: float,
    qfi:    float,
    norm:   float
}

fn qfi_sz_moments(ap: AmpPair, N: int, n_mode: int) -> SzMoments {
    let dim_spin = qfi_pow2(N)
    let mut e1 = 0.0
    let mut e2 = 0.0
    let mut nm = 0.0
    let mut i = 0
    while i < ap.D {
        let s = i - (i / dim_spin) * dim_spin     // i mod dim_spin
        let sz = qfi_sz_value(s, N)
        let prob = ap.re[i] * ap.re[i] + ap.im[i] * ap.im[i]
        e1 = e1 + prob * sz
        e2 = e2 + prob * sz * sz
        nm = nm + prob
        i = i + 1
    }
    let var_sz = e2 - e1 * e1
    let f = 4.0 * var_sz
    return SzMoments { e_sz: e1, e_sz2: e2, var_sz: var_sz, qfi: f, norm: nm }
}

// =============================================================================
//  §7  BASELINE STATES  (SQL: product spin-coherent ; Heisenberg: GHZ)
// =============================================================================
//
//  We embed both baselines in the same spin-motion register (with the mode
//  factored as |0>_mode trivially) so the QFI evaluator is shared.
//
//  SQL: |+>^N (x) |0>_mode    -- product spin-coherent state along +x.
//       <S_z> = 0, <S_z^2> = sum_q <sigma_z^q^2>/4 = N/4 (independent spins)
//       F_phi = 4 * N/4 = N                                     (slope alpha=1)
//
//  Heisenberg / GHZ: (|0>^N + |1>^N)/sqrt(2) (x) |0>_mode
//       <S_z> = 0, <S_z^2> = (1/2)((-N/2)^2 + (N/2)^2) = N^2/4
//       F_phi = N^2                                              (slope alpha=2)

fn qfi_state_sql(N: int, n_mode: int) -> AmpPair {
    let dim_spin = qfi_pow2(N)
    let D = n_mode * dim_spin
    let mut re = []
    let mut im = []
    let mut i = 0
    while i < D {
        re = re.push(0.0)
        im = im.push(0.0)
        i = i + 1
    }
    // |+>^N has uniform 1/sqrt(2^N) amplitude on every computational s; we
    // place all at photon m=0.
    let amp = 1.0 / sqrt(to_float(dim_spin))
    let mut s = 0
    while s < dim_spin {
        re[s] = amp    // m=0 * dim_spin + s = s
        s = s + 1
    }
    return AmpPair { re: re, im: im, D: D }
}

fn qfi_state_ghz(N: int, n_mode: int) -> AmpPair {
    let dim_spin = qfi_pow2(N)
    let D = n_mode * dim_spin
    let mut re = []
    let mut im = []
    let mut i = 0
    while i < D {
        re = re.push(0.0)
        im = im.push(0.0)
        i = i + 1
    }
    let amp = 1.0 / sqrt(2.0)
    re[0] = amp                       // (m=0, s=00...0)
    re[dim_spin - 1] = amp            // (m=0, s=11...1)
    return AmpPair { re: re, im: im, D: D }
}

// =============================================================================
//  §8  LOG-LOG LINEAR FIT  alpha = d(log F) / d(log N)
// =============================================================================
//
//  Ordinary least squares on (log N, log F):
//      alpha = ( Sum (x_i - x_bar)(y_i - y_bar) ) / ( Sum (x_i - x_bar)^2 )
//      x_i = ln N_i ,  y_i = ln F_i .

fn qfi_loglog_slope(Ns: [float], Fs: [float]) -> float {
    let n = len(Ns)
    let mut xs = []
    let mut ys = []
    let mut i = 0
    while i < n {
        xs = xs.push(log(Ns[i]))
        ys = ys.push(log(Fs[i]))
        i = i + 1
    }
    let mut xbar = 0.0
    let mut ybar = 0.0
    let mut j = 0
    while j < n {
        xbar = xbar + xs[j]
        ybar = ybar + ys[j]
        j = j + 1
    }
    xbar = xbar / to_float(n)
    ybar = ybar / to_float(n)
    let mut num = 0.0
    let mut den = 0.0
    let mut k = 0
    while k < n {
        let dx = xs[k] - xbar
        let dy = ys[k] - ybar
        num = num + dx * dy
        den = den + dx * dx
        k = k + 1
    }
    if den < 1.0e-30 { return 0.0 }
    return num / den
}

// =============================================================================
//  §9  RUN THE THREE BASELINES FOR N in {1,2,3,4}
// =============================================================================
//
//  TWO paths for the TC adiabatic state are computed:
//
//    (A) CLOSED-FORM  (paper Eq. (4) verbatim, qfi_closed_form_adiabatic):
//        Maps the truncated, renormalised squeezed-vacuum amplitudes
//        |a_{2n}|^2 onto the final-state spin populations via the paper's
//        own adiabatic argument (paper line 164). This IS the paper's
//        analytical formula and is the canonical metric for the scaling
//        exponent F3. CHEAP: O(n_mode) per N, no matrix work.
//
//    (B) RK4 TIME EVOLUTION  (qfi_adiabatic_ramp): explicit time-dependent
//        Schrodinger solver on the full (n_mode * 2^N) state vector under
//        H_TC(t). Provides the runtime DRIFT witness for F5 and the
//        cross-check that path (A) faithfully captures the dynamics. Run
//        ONLY for small (N, n_mode_rk4) so the interpreter stays under the
//        4 GB heap cap (n_mode_rk4 = 12 keeps D = 192 at N=4 trivial).
//
//  The scaling falsifier F3 uses path (A) at the full r_sq / n_mode_cf
//  parameters; F5 uses path (B) on the smaller register.

struct ScalingRun {
    Ns:      [float],
    F_sql:   [float],
    F_ghz:   [float],
    F_tc:    [float],          // CLOSED-FORM, path (A)
    F_tc_rk4: [float],         // RK4 cross-check (one N only -- N_list[0])
    sq_tails: [float],         // squeezed-vacuum truncation tail per N
    drift_sql_max:  float,
    drift_ghz_max:  float,
    drift_tc_max:   float,     // from path (B)
    rk4_cf_diff_max: float,    // |F_tc_rk4 - F_tc_cf| max across cross-checked Ns
    norm_min:       float,
    norm_max:       float,
    qfi_min:        float,
    alpha_sql:      float,
    alpha_ghz:      float,
    alpha_tc:       float
}

fn qfi_scaling_run(N_list: [int],
                   r_squeeze: float,
                   n_mode_cf: int,          // closed-form Fock cutoff (no memory wall)
                   n_mode_rk4: int,         // RK4 Fock cutoff (memory wall ~ 4GB heap)
                   N_rk4: int,              // run RK4 only for N <= N_rk4
                   Delta0: float, lambda0: float,
                   gamma: float, n_steps: int) -> ScalingRun {
    let mut Ns = []
    let mut F_sql = []
    let mut F_ghz = []
    let mut F_tc  = []
    let mut F_tc_rk4 = []
    let mut sq_tails = []
    let mut drift_sql_max = 0.0
    let mut drift_ghz_max = 0.0
    let mut drift_tc_max  = 0.0
    let mut rk4_cf_diff_max = 0.0
    let mut norm_min = 1.0e30
    let mut norm_max = 0.0
    let mut qfi_min  = 1.0e30
    // SQL / GHZ baselines just need a 1-photon Fock register
    let n_mode_baseline = 1
    // Ramp from t_i = -pi/gamma (where Delta = -Delta_0) to t_f = +pi/gamma
    // (where Delta = +Delta_0).  paper line 185 Fig 2 caption: t_i = -t_f,
    // t_f = pi/gamma, range = 2 pi / gamma.
    let t_i      = 0.0 - 3.14159265358979323846 / gamma
    let t_final  = 3.14159265358979323846 / gamma
    let t_range  = t_final - t_i
    let mut idx = 0
    while idx < len(N_list) {
        let N = N_list[idx]
        // SQL baseline
        let st_sql = qfi_state_sql(N, n_mode_baseline)
        let n_sql = qfi_norm_sq(st_sql)
        if qfi_absf(n_sql - 1.0) > drift_sql_max { drift_sql_max = qfi_absf(n_sql - 1.0) }
        if n_sql < norm_min { norm_min = n_sql }
        if n_sql > norm_max { norm_max = n_sql }
        let mom_sql = qfi_sz_moments(st_sql, N, n_mode_baseline)
        if mom_sql.qfi < qfi_min { qfi_min = mom_sql.qfi }
        // GHZ baseline
        let st_ghz = qfi_state_ghz(N, n_mode_baseline)
        let n_ghz = qfi_norm_sq(st_ghz)
        if qfi_absf(n_ghz - 1.0) > drift_ghz_max { drift_ghz_max = qfi_absf(n_ghz - 1.0) }
        if n_ghz < norm_min { norm_min = n_ghz }
        if n_ghz > norm_max { norm_max = n_ghz }
        let mom_ghz = qfi_sz_moments(st_ghz, N, n_mode_baseline)
        if mom_ghz.qfi < qfi_min { qfi_min = mom_ghz.qfi }
        // TC adiabatic -- CLOSED-FORM path (A): paper Eq. (4) verbatim
        let cf = qfi_closed_form_adiabatic(r_squeeze, N, n_mode_cf)
        if cf.qfi < qfi_min { qfi_min = cf.qfi }
        sq_tails = sq_tails.push(cf.tail)
        // TC adiabatic -- RK4 cross-check path (B), only if N <= N_rk4
        let mut F_rk4_this = 0.0 - 1.0     // sentinel "not run"
        if N < N_rk4 + 1 {
            let init_tc = qfi_state_squeezed_vacuum_allspindown(r_squeeze, N, n_mode_rk4)
            let n_tc0 = qfi_norm_sq(init_tc)
            if n_tc0 < norm_min { norm_min = n_tc0 }
            if n_tc0 > norm_max { norm_max = n_tc0 }
            let ramp = qfi_adiabatic_ramp(init_tc, t_i, t_range, n_steps,
                                           Delta0, lambda0, gamma, N, n_mode_rk4)
            if ramp.norm_drift_max > drift_tc_max { drift_tc_max = ramp.norm_drift_max }
            let n_tc_post = qfi_norm_sq(ramp.state)
            if n_tc_post < norm_min { norm_min = n_tc_post }
            if n_tc_post > norm_max { norm_max = n_tc_post }
            let mom_tc = qfi_sz_moments(ramp.state, N, n_mode_rk4)
            F_rk4_this = mom_tc.qfi
            // For the cross-check, also compute the closed-form at the SAME n_mode_rk4
            // so the comparison apples-to-apples (else the truncation differs)
            let cf_at_rk4 = qfi_closed_form_adiabatic(r_squeeze, N, n_mode_rk4)
            let d = qfi_absf(F_rk4_this - cf_at_rk4.qfi)
            if d > rk4_cf_diff_max { rk4_cf_diff_max = d }
            if mom_tc.qfi < qfi_min { qfi_min = mom_tc.qfi }
        }
        Ns = Ns.push(to_float(N))
        F_sql = F_sql.push(mom_sql.qfi)
        F_ghz = F_ghz.push(mom_ghz.qfi)
        F_tc  = F_tc.push(cf.qfi)            // closed-form is the canonical metric
        F_tc_rk4 = F_tc_rk4.push(F_rk4_this)
        idx = idx + 1
    }
    let a_sql = qfi_loglog_slope(Ns, F_sql)
    let a_ghz = qfi_loglog_slope(Ns, F_ghz)
    let a_tc  = qfi_loglog_slope(Ns, F_tc)
    return ScalingRun {
        Ns: Ns, F_sql: F_sql, F_ghz: F_ghz, F_tc: F_tc, F_tc_rk4: F_tc_rk4,
        sq_tails: sq_tails,
        drift_sql_max: drift_sql_max,
        drift_ghz_max: drift_ghz_max,
        drift_tc_max: drift_tc_max,
        rk4_cf_diff_max: rk4_cf_diff_max,
        norm_min: norm_min, norm_max: norm_max, qfi_min: qfi_min,
        alpha_sql: a_sql, alpha_ghz: a_ghz, alpha_tc: a_tc
    }
}

// =============================================================================
//  §10  FALSIFIER-FIRST SELFTEST  (@D g6  -- FAILED.marker BEFORE pass)
// =============================================================================
//
//  Five falsifier invariants F1-F5:
//
//      F1 : 0.8  <  alpha_SQL          <  1.2     (SQL slope must equal 1)
//      F2 : 1.8  <  alpha_GHZ          <  2.2     (Heisenberg slope must equal 2)
//      F3 : 2.0  <  alpha_TC           <  3.0     (super-Heisenberg; alpha<3 = algebraic ceiling)
//      F4 : F_phi  > -1e-12  always              (QFI non-negative; FD-derivative sanity)
//      F5 : max norm drift  <  1e-9 (SQL/GHZ; product/closed-form construction)
//           AND max norm drift on TC ramp < 1e-3 (RK4 O(dt^4) error budget; the
//           cosmetic post-renorm absorbs it but the raw drift is the witness)
//
//  TC engine knobs (justified by paper sec II):
//      n_mode    = 8                 (Fock cutoff; sinh^2 r=1.0 ~= 1.38 photons << 7)
//      r_squeeze = 1.0               (modest -- safe within n_mode=8; z=tanh^2 r=0.580)
//      Delta_0   = 4.0               (dispersive: |Delta_max| >> lambda_max)
//      lambda_0  = 1.0
//      gamma     = 0.2               (slow ramp; t_final = pi/gamma = 15.7)
//      n_steps   = 80                (dt = 0.196 -- RK4 step error << 1)

struct FalsifierReport {
    pass:        int,
    F1_alpha_sql:   float,
    F2_alpha_ghz:   float,
    F3_alpha_tc:    float,
    F4_qfi_min:     float,
    F5_drift_max:   float,
    F5_drift_tc:    float,
    F6_rk4_cf_diff: float,
    qfi_sql_N4:     float,
    qfi_ghz_N4:     float,
    qfi_tc_N4:      float,
    Ns:             [float],
    F_sql:          [float],
    F_ghz:          [float],
    F_tc:           [float],
    F_tc_rk4:       [float],
    sq_tails:       [float],
    wall_seconds:   float,
    notes:          [str]
}

fn qfi_run_falsifiers() -> FalsifierReport {
    let t0 = to_int(exec("date +%s").trim())
    let N_list = [1, 2, 3, 4]
    // Closed-form path -- the canonical scaling-exponent metric (path A).
    // n_mode_cf=64 is far below any memory wall (it's O(n_mode_cf) per N) and
    // captures the strong-squeezing regime (r=5.0, sinh^2(5)/2 ~ 33 photons,
    // truncated at 63; the truncation tail is reported as INFO).
    let n_mode_cf = 64
    let r_sq   = 5.0
    // RK4 cross-check path (B) -- only used at small (N, n_mode_rk4) so it
    // fits in the hexa-run interpreter's 4 GB heap with ~ 12 buffers of
    // length D = n_mode_rk4 * 2^N. n_mode_rk4=12, N_rk4=3 gives D=96,
    // 12*96 = 1152 float scratch entries per state -- trivially in the cap.
    let n_mode_rk4 = 8
    let N_rk4      = 2
    let Delta0 = 4.0
    let lam0   = 1.0
    let gamma  = 0.2
    let n_step = 500
    let run = qfi_scaling_run(N_list, r_sq, n_mode_cf, n_mode_rk4, N_rk4,
                               Delta0, lam0, gamma, n_step)
    let mut pass = 1
    let mut notes = []
    notes = notes.push("Path (A) closed-form F_phi (paper Eq.(4)): n_mode_cf=" + str(n_mode_cf) + ", r=" + str(r_sq))
    notes = notes.push("Path (B) RK4 cross-check: n_mode_rk4=" + str(n_mode_rk4) + ", N<=" + str(N_rk4) + ", n_step=" + str(n_step))
    // F1
    let f1_ok = if run.alpha_sql > 0.8 {
        if run.alpha_sql < 1.2 { 1 } else { 0 }
    } else { 0 }
    if f1_ok == 0 { pass = 0 }
    notes = notes.push("F1  alpha_SQL                = " + str(run.alpha_sql) + "    (target 1, in (0.8, 1.2))")
    // F2
    let f2_ok = if run.alpha_ghz > 1.8 {
        if run.alpha_ghz < 2.2 { 1 } else { 0 }
    } else { 0 }
    if f2_ok == 0 { pass = 0 }
    notes = notes.push("F2  alpha_GHZ                = " + str(run.alpha_ghz) + "    (target 2, in (1.8, 2.2))")
    // F3
    let f3_ok = if run.alpha_tc > 2.0 {
        if run.alpha_tc < 3.0 { 1 } else { 0 }
    } else { 0 }
    if f3_ok == 0 { pass = 0 }
    notes = notes.push("F3  alpha_TC (closed-form)   = " + str(run.alpha_tc) + "    (target ~5/2, in (2.0, 3.0); paper Eq.(5) asymptotic)")
    // F4
    let f4_ok = if run.qfi_min > 0.0 - 1.0e-12 { 1 } else { 0 }
    if f4_ok == 0 { pass = 0 }
    notes = notes.push("F4  min(F_phi)               = " + str(run.qfi_min) + "    (target >= 0, tol 1e-12)")
    // F5 split: SQL/GHZ closed-form construction < 1e-9; TC RK4 < 1e-3
    let drift_closed = qfi_max2(run.drift_sql_max, run.drift_ghz_max)
    let f5a_ok = if drift_closed < 1.0e-9 { 1 } else { 0 }
    let f5b_ok = if run.drift_tc_max < 1.0e-3 { 1 } else { 0 }
    if f5a_ok == 0 { pass = 0 }
    if f5b_ok == 0 { pass = 0 }
    notes = notes.push("F5a max norm drift (SQL/GHZ closed-form construction) = " + str(drift_closed) + "    (tol 1e-9)")
    notes = notes.push("F5b max norm drift (TC RK4 ramp, N<=" + str(N_rk4) + ", n_mode_rk4=" + str(n_mode_rk4) + ")         = " + str(run.drift_tc_max) + "    (tol 1e-3)")
    // F6: RK4 vs closed-form agreement (info-grade -- a soft cross-check of
    // dynamics-vs-paper-formula; the unitary RK4 with finite dt and the
    // closed-form adiabatic limit can disagree at the percent level since
    // the RK4 carries Landau-Zener leakage that the closed-form ignores;
    // we still gate to a generous 1.0 absolute -- the QFI per N is O(1)-O(10)).
    let f6_ok = if run.rk4_cf_diff_max < 1.0 { 1 } else { 0 }
    if f6_ok == 0 { pass = 0 }
    notes = notes.push("F6  max |F_TC(RK4) - F_TC(closed-form)| at N<=" + str(N_rk4) + " = " + str(run.rk4_cf_diff_max) +
                       "    (tol 1.0 abs; soft cross-check that RK4 dynamics tracks paper Eq.(4))")
    // F_phi by N for each baseline -- diagnostic
    let mut k = 0
    while k < len(run.Ns) {
        let rk4_str = if run.F_tc_rk4[k] < 0.0 - 0.5 { "n/a" } else { str(run.F_tc_rk4[k]) }
        notes = notes.push("    N=" + str(to_int(run.Ns[k])) +
                           "  F_SQL=" + str(run.F_sql[k]) +
                           "  F_GHZ=" + str(run.F_ghz[k]) +
                           "  F_TC(cf)=" + str(run.F_tc[k]) +
                           "  F_TC(rk4)=" + rk4_str +
                           "  sq_tail=" + str(run.sq_tails[k]))
        k = k + 1
    }
    // Closed-form anchors for sanity (reported as INFO -- not gates)
    notes = notes.push("INFO closed-form anchors at N=4: F_SQL_closed = 4.0,  F_GHZ_closed = 16.0  (Heisenberg ceiling F<=N^2)")
    let z_5 = qfi_tanh(r_sq) * qfi_tanh(r_sq)
    let pref5 = (256.0 * sqrt(1.0 - z_5)) / (15.0 * sqrt(3.14159265358979323846))
    notes = notes.push("INFO paper Eq.(5) asymptotic prefactor at r=" + str(r_sq) + " (z=tanh^2(r)=" + str(z_5) + "):  256 sqrt(1-z)/(15 sqrt(pi)) = " + str(pref5))
    notes = notes.push("INFO paper Eq.(5) F_max(N=4) = " + str(pref5 * qfi_powf(2.0, 2.5)) + "  (asymptotic z->1 limit, comparison only)")
    let t1 = to_int(exec("date +%s").trim())
    let wall = to_float(t1 - t0)
    // pluck N=4 (the last entry)
    let last = len(run.Ns) - 1
    return FalsifierReport {
        pass: pass,
        F1_alpha_sql: run.alpha_sql,
        F2_alpha_ghz: run.alpha_ghz,
        F3_alpha_tc:  run.alpha_tc,
        F4_qfi_min:   run.qfi_min,
        F5_drift_max: drift_closed,
        F5_drift_tc:  run.drift_tc_max,
        F6_rk4_cf_diff: run.rk4_cf_diff_max,
        qfi_sql_N4:   run.F_sql[last],
        qfi_ghz_N4:   run.F_ghz[last],
        qfi_tc_N4:    run.F_tc[last],
        Ns: run.Ns, F_sql: run.F_sql, F_ghz: run.F_ghz, F_tc: run.F_tc,
        F_tc_rk4: run.F_tc_rk4, sq_tails: run.sq_tails,
        wall_seconds: wall,
        notes: notes
    }
}

// =============================================================================
//  §11  MARKER  (falsifier-first per @D g6 -- FAILED path FIRST in selftest)
// =============================================================================

fn qfi_emit_marker(passed: int, body: str) -> int {
    let ts = exec("date +%s").trim()
    let qm_root = env("QMIRROR_ROOT")
    let root = if qm_root.len() > 0 { qm_root } else { exec("pwd").trim() }
    let marker_dir = root + "/state/markers"
    let _mk = exec("mkdir -p " + marker_dir + " 2>/dev/null")
    let suffix = if passed == 1 { ".marker" } else { "_FAILED.marker" }
    let path = marker_dir + "/qfi_spin_motion_" + ts + suffix
    let _w = exec("echo '" + body + "' > '" + path + "'")
    println("  marker: " + path)
    return 0
}

fn qfi_selftest() -> int {
    let rep = qfi_run_falsifiers()
    let mut i = 0
    while i < len(rep.notes) {
        println("  " + rep.notes[i])
        i = i + 1
    }
    println("  wall = " + str(rep.wall_seconds) + "s")
    let body = "qfi_spin_motion selftest; " +
        "alpha_SQL=" + str(rep.F1_alpha_sql) +
        " alpha_GHZ=" + str(rep.F2_alpha_ghz) +
        " alpha_TC=" + str(rep.F3_alpha_tc) +
        " min(F)=" + str(rep.F4_qfi_min) +
        " drift_closed=" + str(rep.F5_drift_max) +
        " drift_TC=" + str(rep.F5_drift_tc) +
        " rk4_cf_diff=" + str(rep.F6_rk4_cf_diff) +
        " F_SQL(N=4)=" + str(rep.qfi_sql_N4) +
        " F_GHZ(N=4)=" + str(rep.qfi_ghz_N4) +
        " F_TC(N=4)=" + str(rep.qfi_tc_N4) +
        " wall=" + str(rep.wall_seconds) + "s"
    // Falsifier-first: FAILED.marker BEFORE pass.
    if rep.pass == 1 {
        // fall through to pass marker
    } else {
        let _ = qfi_emit_marker(0, "FAIL " + body)
        return 0
    }
    let _ = qfi_emit_marker(1, "PASS " + body)
    return 1
}

// =============================================================================
//  §12  MAIN
// =============================================================================

fn main() {
    println("[qmirror/qfi-spin-motion] EXACT QFI = 4 Var(S_z) on adiabatic Tavis-Cummings spin-motion states")
    println("  paper  = arXiv:2411.10117 (super-Heisenberg F_phi ~ N^{5/2} ; Eq.(1) H_TC ; Eq.(4) F_phi ; Eq.(5) asymptotic)")
    println("  H_TC   = Delta(t) S_z + (lambda(t)/sqrt(N)) ( S+ a + S- a^dag )")
    println("  ramp   = Delta(t)=Delta_0 sin(gamma t/2),  lambda(t)=lambda_0 cos^2(gamma t/2),  t in [-pi/gamma, pi/gamma]")
    println("  init   = |all-down>_spin  (x)  |squeezed-vacuum>_mode(r)")
    println("  QFI    = 4 ( <psi|S_z^2|psi> - <psi|S_z|psi>^2 )    (closed-form, generator R_z=exp(-i phi S_z); F<=N^2 always)")
    println("  paths  = (A) closed-form per paper Eq.(4) -- canonical, O(n_mode) per N, scales to n_mode=64")
    println("           (B) RK4 time-dep Schrodinger -- cross-check, capped at small (N, n_mode_rk4) for hexa-run RAM budget")
    println("  ceil   = bosonic-mode truncation (closed-form: n_mode_cf=64 ; RK4: n_mode_rk4=12 @ N<=3 to fit interpreter)")
    println("  free   = SQL slope alpha=1 (closed form), Heisenberg slope alpha=2 (GHZ closed form)")
    if qfi_selftest() == 1 {
        println("[qmirror/qfi-spin-motion] SELFTEST PASS  " +
                "(6 falsifier invariants F1-F6 cleared; SQL slope ~ 1, Heisenberg slope ~ 2, TC slope in (2, 3), RK4 ~= closed-form)")
        println("__QMIRROR_QFI_SPIN_MOTION__ PASS")
    } else {
        println("[qmirror/qfi-spin-motion] SELFTEST FAIL  " +
                "(at least one falsifier triggered; see *_FAILED.marker)")
        println("__QMIRROR_QFI_SPIN_MOTION__ FAIL")
    }
}
